A palindrome is a word or phrase that is the same forward and backward, ignoring spaces and punctuation. For example, “racecar” and “Madam, I’m Adam” are palindromes. Assume that the parameter is not null and that it contains at least one character.

To determine whether a String is a palindrome, we can use a for loop to iterate over the characters of the String and swap them if they are in the same position. Then, we can return a boolean value to indicate whether the String was successfully swapped or not.

public boolean isPalindrome(String s) {

  if (s == null || s.length() == 0) {
    return false;
  }

  for (int i = 0, j = s.length() - 1; i < j; i++, j--) {
    char temp = s.charAt(i);
    s = s.substring(0, i) + s.substring(j);
    s = s.substring(0, j) + temp;
  }
  return s.equals(s.substring(0, s.length() - 1));
}

